esting in place!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is required for meaningful Vert.x Web Client coverage, but 5.0.1 still resolves Netty 4.2.x and should carry the native-runtime unsafe-access system properties already needed by 5.0.0 on JDK 25.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure the generated test/native runtime for io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 with system properties `-Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow` and `-Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true`; do not leave them gated only to version 5.0.0. Meaningful tests can use an in-process Vert.x `HttpServer` on loopback for GET/POST, JSON, forms, multipart upload, redirects, cookies/sessions, caching, and response predicates; no external service is needed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact exposes `OAuth2WebClient`, whose signatures reference the optional `io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2` module. Do not target OAuth2-specific coverage unless adding that optional test dependency deliberately; core Web Client coverage is meaningful without it.\",\n    \"Native-image verification remains authoritative because the known Netty/JDK 25 unsafe-access behavior is runtime-sensitive.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_000821b290e9cd40016a4149f2580481978feb856d0ae0b981\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 319, "output": 1674, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31177, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782663645504, "responseId": "resp_000821b290e9cd40016a4149de5d3881979f4e10de68d670b7"}, "toolResults": []}
